      • onPageModeCleared

        public void onPageModeCleared()
        Delete everything associated with any queue on this address. This is to be called when the address is about to be released from paging. Hence the PagingStore will be holding a write lock, meaning no messages are going to be paged at this time. So, we shouldn't lock anything after this method, to avoid dead locks between the writeLock and any synchronization with the CursorProvider.
        Specified by:
        onPageModeCleared in interface PageCursorProvider
